            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="./DCP-LETT-9619.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Letter from Charles Lyell, 1 September 1874</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_7291.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Maria Sophia Heathcote</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">The postscript to the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9619.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Charles Lyell, 1 September 1874</ref>, had not been found when the letter was published in <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 22, but has since been found; see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 30, Supplement.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">CD stayed with <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1245.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Erasmus Darwin</ref> in Southampton from 30 July to 24 August 1874 (CD’s ‘Journal’ (Appendix II)).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3854.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Joseph Prestwich</ref> had discussed drift deposits in southern England in Prestwich 1862.</note>
